{
    "name": "Greensting Scorpion",
    "type": "monster",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Ecology",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "<b>Environment</b> warm or temperate forests<br/><b>Organization</b> solitary, pair, or colony (3\u20136)<br/><b>Treasure</b> none"
        },
        {
            "name": "Special Abilities",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "<b>Poison (Ex)</b> Sting\u2014injury; <i>save </i>Fort DC 10; <i>frequency </i>1/round for 6 rounds; <i>effect </i>sickened for 1 round; <i>cure </i>1 save. The save DC is Constitution-based."
        },
        {
            "name": "Description",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "Deadly greensting scorpions normally live in forests, though they can survive nearly anywhere.<br/><br/>A greensting scorpion familiar grants a +4 bonus on Initiative checks so long as the familiar is within 1 mile of the spellcaster. A greensting scorpion familiar loses the mindless trait and has an Intelligence score appropriate for its master\u2019s level."
        }
    ],
    "html": "<i>Though its pincers seem too small to harm anything larger than an insect, this scorpion\u2019s stinger still appears dangerous.</i>",
